This MENU define the CHARACTERISTICS of the DRAWING in 3D
Notably the visible rectangle on display

19: REDUCTION % of FACES
to see better the position of edges of faces

22: GROW by 2 MOUSE clicks at Min MAX
With the mouse, click the corner MINIMUM and MAXIMUM
All PSLVO which are in this frame will be drawn on display

23: REDUCE by 2 MOUSE clicks
With the mouse, click 2 points such that the totality of
the actual window will occupy in the future window.

24: TRANSLATE by 2 MOUSE clicks
With the mouse, define a first  point P1
With the mouse, define a second point P2
The drawing is translated of a vector P1P2

25: 2D WINDOW [Xmin MAX] [Ymin MAX]
Define the 2D object WINDOW for the future drawings.

26: RE-DEFINITION of EXTREMAL XYZ
Define the new extremal coordinates MIN MAX of PLSVO
to draw on the display.
Give ZMIN=ZMAX=0 in 2D
Only the PLSVO interior of this hexahedron will be drawn

27: Total SCENE from EXTREMAL XYZ
Only the PLSVO interior of the actual MIN MAX hexahedron
will be drawn

30: LONGITUDE & LATITUDE in degrees
The drawing uses a trimetric axonometrie to conserve the distances
The SEEN POINT is unchanged.
By default, it is the barycentre of the MIN MAX hexahedron.
The X-AXIS which pass by the SEEN POINT define the ANGLE
of NULL LONGITUDE in the plane XY.
The LONGITUDE belongs to [-180,180] degrees.
The LATITUDE is the ANGLE between the XY PLANE and the line
SEEN POINT-EYE and belongs to [-90,90] degrees.
Default values are: 40 degrees of LONGITUDE
                and 20 degrees of LATITUDE

31: XYZ of the SEEN POINT & the EYE
to define the direction of view

32: Half WIDTH & HEIGHT of the SCENE

33: PLANE Behind Front of SEEN POINT
Give the distance >0 or <0 from the seen point of 2 planes
orthogonal to the view direction. 
Only FE between these 2 planes will be drawn.
Thus you can see at the interior of a closed surface!

34: ZOOMING of the Drawing
Give the growing factor of the drawing
If this value = 2, the width and heigth of SCENE reduces to half
    >1 => growing   of the drawing object
    <1 => reduction of the drawing object

35: ROTATION around Z-axis in degrees
Give the LONGITUDE around the vertical Z-axis
  
36: CHANGE the PALETTE of COLORS
Give the number from 1 to 16 to define the palette of colors
1: The COLORS vary quickly and darken. The intensity decreases
2: Les COLORS vary quickly and darken.
3: RAINBOW Palette
4: Palette from CYAN    to BLUE  then to BLUE  BLACK.
5: Palette from YELLOW  to RED   then to RED   BLACK.
6: Palette from YELLOW  to GREEN then to GREEN BLACK.
7: Palette from MAGENTA to RED   then to RED   BLACK.
8: Palette from MAGENTA to BLUE  then to BLUE  BLACK. 
9: Palette from CYAN    to GREEN then to GREEN BLACK.
10:Palette of 256 GRAYS         
11:Palette RAINBOW LIGHT WITHOUT GREEN for COLOR ISOVALUES ZONES
12:Palette from BLUE to RED by GREEN YELLOW ORANGE
   to the FE qualities
13:Palette from RED to YELLOW to GREEN with BLACK ADDED to COLORS
14:Palette    CONTINUOUS RAINBOW for COLOR ISOVALUES ZONES
15:Palette DISCONTINUOUS RAINBOW for COLOR ISOVALUES ZONES
16:Palette CONTINUOUS BLUE WHITE RED for COLOR ISOVALUES ZONES

38: BACK to the DEFAULT COLORS
All default colors, palette, ... are imposed.

39: BACKGROUND COLOR
Give the new color of the window background

44: DRAW a TEXT on the SCREEN
Click a point and type a text

47: 3 FAR FACES of GLOBAL HEXAEDRON
The 3 farest FACES of the MIN-MAX coordinate HEXAHEDRON
will be drawn and completed with the options:

  0: NO DRAWING
     Suppress this type of drawings

  1: Only 8 GLOBAL EDGES are drawn

  2: QUADRILATERAL GRIDS
     The 3 faces are drawn with quadrilateral grids
     without background color

  3: BACKGROUND of 3 FACES has the same color

  4: CHESS-BOARD with 2 COLORS on the 3 FACES
     The 3 faces are drawn with quadrangles of alternated colors
     The edge greatest length is cut into 10 + 2 margins
     The 2 other dimensions are adjusted to an integer number

48: 3 SEEN EDGES of GLOBAL HEXAEDRON
The 3 nearest edges of the global hexahedron for the eye
will be drawn immediately.

49: REFERENCE SYSTEM AXIS of PLSVO
Some different representations of the reference axis are possible

50: ERASE the WINDOW

60: FRAME a drawing to improve the scene
by 2 clicks at MIN and MAX corners.

75: Activate TRANSLATION ORBIT ZOOM
permit to use the buttons of the mouse after the option 90;
left   button => Translation
middle button => @ in 2D, rotations in 3d
right  button => Zoom + or -

76: Stop the TRANSLATION ORBIT ZOOM
suppress the effect of option 75;

90: EXECUTE the DRAWING
Draw with the drawing characteristics defined before
colors, type of lines, ...
